Class JCObjectSaver

java.lang.Object
  java.io.OutputStream
      java.io.ObjectOutputStream
          net.nawaman.javacompiler.JCObjectSaver
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Closeable, java.io.DataOutput, java.io.Flushable, java.io.ObjectOutput, java.io.ObjectStreamConstants
public class JCObjectSaver
extends java.io.ObjectOutputStream

Write an object to a stream and takes care of all the class data. Use this class with JCObjectLoader as they maintain the same protocol. Using JCObjectLoader/JCObjectSaver rather than JavaCompiler as you do not need to worry about the writing of object. IMPORTANT NOTE: The close(...) method of this class MUST BE CALLED to endure all the data is saved. This is a weak point of the techique as it wait until all objects are wirtten to be sure that all class-data are saved and that is when close(...) is called.
